    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-12-08T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-12-08T17:00:00-05:00" n="306"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/565: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Panama (<persName corresp="#p_DRT1"
                            type="from">Davis</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-08T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 8, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>168. Referring to my telegram No. 167, December 8, 4 p.m. For <persName
                        corresp="#p_WF1">White</persName> from <persName corresp="#p_DA1"
                        >Dawson</persName>.<note n="27" xml:id="d306fn27">
                        <persName corresp="#p_DA1">Allen Dawson</persName>, Second Secretary of
                        Legation in Colombia, then on board the S.S. <hi rend="italic">Santa
                            Barbara</hi> with Señor <persName corresp="#p_CTM1">Cruchaga</persName>
                        en route from New York to Buenaventura. (721.23/628).</note>
                </p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“When <persName corresp="#p_CTM1">Cruchaga</persName> outlined his ‘formula’
                        I pointed out that <persName corresp="#p_OHE1">Olaya</persName> has insisted
                        he could not enter into any discussion of changes in 1922 treaty until in
                        possession of Leticia. <persName corresp="#p_CTM1">Cruchaga</persName> then
                        said that he would see that first act of commission was to order return of
                        seized territory and asked that I get word of this to <persName
                            corresp="#p_OHE1">Olaya</persName> upon reaching Bogotá. <persName
                            corresp="#p_OHE1">Olaya</persName> will not of course be satisfied with
                        this.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DRT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
